iron.ui

These classes handle interaction with the user.

Main

The main entry point of the application. This class starts the system and connects the UI layer to the service and iron.core layers.

MainMenu

Represents the main menu of the system. This class displays high-level options for racers, organizers, and administrators.

RacerMenu

Provides racer-specific menu options. This includes actions like buying a license, registering for a race, viewing race history, and leaving reviews.

OrganizerMenu

Provides organizer-specific menu options. This includes creating races, managing race details, and entering results.

AdminMenu

Provides administrator-specific menu options. This includes managing users, licenses, and overall settings.

RaceScreen

Displays race information to the user. This class may show race details, registration deadlines, categories, and participant limits.

RegistrationScreen

Handles the UI flow for race registration. This class gathers racer input and passes it to the appropriate service.

ReviewScreen

Handles the UI flow for leaving race reviews. This class collects review information from racers and sends it to the review logic.